
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-sajassi-l2vpn-pbb-evpn-03.txt'>
    <title>"PBB E-VPN", Ali Sajassi, Lizhong Jin, Nabil Bitar, Samer Salam, Sami Boutros</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-sajassi-l2vpn-pbb-evpn-03.txt</link>
    <description>This document discusses how Ethernet Provider Backbone Bridging [802.1ah] can be combined with E-VPN in order to reduce the number of BGP MAC advertisement routes by aggregating Customer/Client MAC (C-MAC) addresses via Provider Backbone MAC address (B-MAC), provide client MAC address mobility using C-MAC aggregation and B-MAC sub- netting, confine the scope of C-MAC learning to only active flows, offer per site policies and avoid C-MAC address flushing on topology changes. The combined solution is referred to as PBB-EVPN.  Conventions</description>
    <dc:date>2011-10-30T23:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
